    • Constructor Detail

      • Community

        public Community(java.lang.String name,
                 java.lang.String representantName,
                 java.lang.String representantPhone,
                 int population,
                 int intChallenge,
                 int intType)

        Communty

        Description: Initializes and creates an instance of Community. The name, representantName,representantPhone, and population are used exactly as they are entered. For intChallenge and intType, they are first converted to a Challenge and CommunityType literal first.

        Preconditions:

        • name must be a String.
        • representantName must be a String.
        • representantPhone must be a String.
        • population must be an int.
        • intChallenge must be an int between 1 and 4.
        • population must be an int between 1 and 3.

        Postconditions:

        • An instance of Community is created with all the necessary parameters.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the Community.
        representantName - The name of the person that represents the community.
        representantPhone - The phone number of the community's representant.
        population - The number of people that live in the community.
        intChallenge - The chosen option from the list of Challenge descriptions.
        intType - The chosen option from the list of CommunityType descriptions.

    • Method Detail

      • addProduct

        public java.lang.String addProduct(Product newProduct)

        addProduct

        Description: Uses the entered product to then save in the producs array and returns a success message. First, it checks if there is a duplicate product with the same name already existing within the community. If so, a duplicate message is returned. Second, it checks if there is space to register a new product within the community. If not, a no space message will be returned.

        Preconditions:

        • newProduct must be a valid instance of Product. Non-null.

        Postconditions:

        • If a product with the same name already exists within the community, a duplicate message is returned.
        • If there is no more space to register a new product within the community, a no space message is returned.
        • Otherwise, the new product is added to the products array, and a success message is returned.
        Parameters:
        newProduct - The product instance to be added to the community.
        Returns:
        A message stating if the product was added successfully or not (stating the reason if it wasn't successful).

      • deleteProduct

        public java.lang.String deleteProduct(int intProduct)

        deleteProduct

        Description: Deletes a product from the community based on the specified product index.

        Preconditions:

        • intProduct must be an int representing a valid index of a product within the community.

        Postconditions:

        • The product at the specified index is removed from the community, and a success message is returned.
        Parameters:
        intProduct - The index of the product to be deleted from the community.
        Returns:
        A message indicating that the product was successfully deleted.

      • searchProduct

        public boolean searchProduct(java.lang.String productName)

        searchProduct

        Description: Verifies if the entered product name already exists in the array of products. It will loop through all the existing products and check if the name matches the entered product name.

        Preconditions:

        • Array holding the products must already exist.
        • productName has to be a String.

        Postconditions:

        • A boolean indicating if a duplicate was found or not.
        Parameters:
        productName - The name of the product to be searched for in the products array.
        Returns:
        A boolean indicating if there is a duplicate or not.

      • availableProduct

        public int availableProduct()

        availableProduct

        Description: Verifies if there is an empty space in the array of products in order to save another product afterwards. It will loop through the products array and check if each element is equal to null. If an element is null, it returns the index of that element. If there are no null elements, it will return -1.

        Preconditions:

        • Array holding the products must already exist.

        Postconditions:

        • An int holding the index of the last null element in the products array will be returned. If there is no more space, -1 will be returned instead.
        Returns:
        An int holding the index of the last null element in the products array (if there is no more space, -1 will be returned).

      • oneMinProduct

        public boolean oneMinProduct()

        oneMinProduct

        Description: Checks if at least one product was registered already.

        Preconditions:

        • Array of products must already exist.

        Postconditions:

        • A boolean value indicating if the first position in the products array is occupied or not is returned.
        Returns:
        true if the first position of the products array is filled, false otherwise.

      • displayProducts

        public java.lang.String displayProducts()

        displayProducts

        Description: Concatenates and returns a string that holds all the descriptions of the products within the community. It iterates through the products array, assigns a number to each product, and extracts the product names. It makes sure that no null product is passed on to prevent a Null Exception.

        Preconditions:

        • products must be in place and initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • A String holding all the numbered product names in order will be returned.
        Returns:
        A String containing all the numbered product names within the community.
